when we create ec2 we give secrity groups ( turnon the traffic we need like ssh 22, http 80, https 443)
so no need to the UFW ( inside linux seperately) 
This UFW is like an optional second layer and it is disabled by aws setups by default as we already give security groups to server

AWS Security Group is the PRIMARY firewall
UFW is SECONDARY (inside Linux)

You can allow both but sometimes, few requests aws can allow but ufw may not allow or ufw may allow and aws may not allow. so better to always keep aws securoty group on

if you want to allow ufw then code:

Check:
sudo ufw status

Allow:
sudo ufw allow ssh
sudo ufw allow 80
sudo ufw allow 443

Enable:
sudo ufw enable

Verify:
sudo ufw status
